                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Fragments of three poorly preserved documents that were found close together. The three documents are put together from ﬁve roll-pieces. There are certain similarities in the contents of all the three papyri. They all seem to deal with taxes and landed property.</summary>
                        <msItemStruct>
                            <note type="general">The original total length of 81B must have been at least 260 cm, written transversa charta. All that is preserved are fragments coming from a narrow strip with a maximum width of 5.7 cm. The beginning of the text, containing an upper margin of approximately 10 cm, was in the core. Toward the end of the text, one can distinguish various hands, indicating signatures and some empty layers, possibly representing the bottom margin and thus the end of the document, even though there is some writing again in the few very last layers..</note>
                            <note type="general">Reproduced in plates CLIII–CLIV</note>
                            <note type="local_note">Field no. XXIXm1</note>
